SIMPLE: mise
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mise
<hw>Mise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>mise</ets> a
putting, setting, expense, fr. <ets>mis</ets>, <ets>mise</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>mettre</ets> to put, lay, fr. LL. <ets>mittere</ets> to
send.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The issue in a writ of
right.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expense; cost; disbursement.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A tax or tallage; in Wales, an honorary gift of the
people to a new king or prince of Wales; also, a tribute paid, in the
country palatine of Chester, England, at the change of the owner of the
earldom.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misease</ent>⟦br⟧
